PART II  -  ESTABLISHMENT OF  RURAL ELECTRIFICATION MANAGEMENT COMMITTEE
* the Director of Energy Affairs in the Department of Energy Affairs.
* The Chief Executive of the Authority or his/her designated represetantive;
* The Principal Secretary of the Department of Economic Planning and Development;
* The Secretary to the Treasury;
* The Principal Secretary of the Ministry of Local Government;
* A representative of the Board of Engineers;
* A representative of the Society of Accountants ofMalawi.

The objectives of the Committee shall be -
* to ensure that the majority of the Malawian population in peri-urban and rural communities have access to efficient, sustainable and affordable energy for their social economic development through grid extension and off grid electricity supply, including solar home system technologies;
<\li1>
	* to raise funds and receive and administer the Fund for the benefit of rural electrification in Malawi;
	* to prepare annual rural electrification programme(s) and advise the Minister on the prioritization, selection criteria on candidate sites, and ensure the efficient and effective implementation of rural electrification programmes;
	* to promote rural electrification and act as a source of technical, commercial and institutional advice in rural electrification matters.

The annual report referred to in subsection (1) shall  include -
* an audited balance sheet and statement of cash flow and income and expenditure;
* a report of the examination of the accounts referred to in section 21 (3) (b);
* a status report on rural electrification;
* a report regarding rural electrification programme for the next financial year;
* a list of Concessionaires and beneficiaries who have benefited from the Fund or the Credit Guarantee;
* a report on the performance of Concessionaires with respect to rural electrification projects in progress, planned and completed.
